##Ministry of Agriculture and Rural Areas: poultry industry serious losses, the loss of more than 100 million individual enterprises

Yang Zhenhai, director of the Animal Husbandry and Veterinary Bureau of the Ministry of Agriculture, said that since the outbreak, live poultry trading markets have been closed and the transportation of feed, poultry and live poultry has been blocked. In addition, poultry slaughter enterprises stopped production, poultry products consumption, the loss of the entire poultry industry is very serious.



On February 18,2020, the State Council's Joint Prevention and Control Mechanism held a press conference on the work of "vegetable basket" to ensure stable production and supply. Regarding the overall operation of the current agricultural products market, Song Danyang, deputy director of the Department of Marketing and Information Technology of the Ministry of Agriculture and rural areas, introduced at the press conference that after the outbreak of the new coronavirus pneumonia, looking at the national situation, the market supply of key "vegetable basket" products is generally adequate, market operation is basically stable, and market prices rise and fall.

Since the Spring Festival, the average wholesale price of pork has increased slightly and stabilized at around 50 yuan per kilogram. On February 17, the average price of pork in the national wholesale market was 50.8 yuan per kilogram, 7.6 percent higher than before the Spring Festival. The price of vegetables fluctuated slightly, the average price of the 28 vegetables monitored on February 17 was 5.83 yuan per kg, 7.2% higher than that before the Spring Festival. The price of fruits showed little change. The average wholesale price of the six fruits monitored on February 17 was 5.65 yuan per kg, which was slightly lower than that before the Spring Festival Eggs, chicken prices run weak, than before the Chinese New Year fell.

There have been reports that some breeding enterprises encountered a shortage of feed, the impact of the outbreak on the poultry industry how much? Yang Zhenhai, director of the Animal Husbandry and Veterinary Bureau of the Ministry of Agriculture, said that since the outbreak, live poultry trading markets have been closed and the transportation of feed, poultry and live poultry has been blocked. In addition, poultry slaughter enterprises stopped production, poultry products consumption, the loss of the entire poultry industry is very serious.

"Some companies have reported losses of more than 100m yuan. If this situation continues, our analysis may have some impact on the supply of poultry meat and eggs to the market in the second and third quarters,"Yang said.

Yang Zhenhai, has initially ruled out the source of new pneumonia and the relationship between known poultry and livestock. The Ministry of Agriculture and rural areas will coordinate the relevant departments to implement the classified management of live poultry trading markets, organize the butchering enterprises to coordinate with poultry farm households, implement the centralized butchering and listing, and ensure that live poultry are not pressed into the market.

On ensuring feed supply, Yang Zhenhai said that as of February 17,6,384 of the 9,711 feed enterprises nationwide had resumed production, with a start-up rate of 66 percent, but there was still a certain gap between the start-up rate of enterprises and that of the same period in a year-round, however, "as long as the traffic problem is solved, it will return to normal gradually, and the total supply should not be a problem. "

In response to the two poultry influenza A virus subtype H5N1 outbreaks in Shaoyang and Nanchong this year, Yang Zhenhai said that the incidence of avian influenza in China is very low, both among poultry and among humans, we do not need to "talk about poultry color change" , can rest assured that the quarantine qualified, legally listed poultry products.

According to reports, in February, a influenza A virus subtype H5N1 epidemic broke out in Shaoyang, Hunan Province, and in Nanchong, Sichuan Province. Both farms are small and medium-sized farms, with 10,347 birds stored in poultry stalls and 6,340 birds killed. The handling of the epidemic has now been completed, a total of 28,214 poultry in the affected areas were culled. After the local animal husbandry and veterinary department check, the surrounding poultry farms have no abnormal situation. The local health department monitoring, close contact people are currently clinical health, sampling and monitoring were negative.

"according to experts' analysis, the two outbreaks are more likely to be spread by wild birds, which can be said to be 'disaster from heaven and poison from birds' , which also warns us that the wide contamination of pathogens of major animal epidemics, the many ways of spread, and the difficulty of prevention and control, must not be taken lightly, " Yang said.

Pan Wenbo, director-general of the Department of Crop Management of the Ministry of Agriculture and rural areas, also revealed at the press conference that this year's spring ploughing has also encountered some new situations and new problems as a result of the new crown pneumonia epidemic.

Pan Wenbo said that at present, many agricultural enterprises need the approval of the local epidemic prevention and Control Headquarters to start work, plus workers, technical personnel can not be in place in time, the normal resumption of production rate is relatively low. Secondly, it is difficult for agricultural means of production to reach the village. At present, the total supply of agricultural means such as seeds, chemical fertilizers and pesticides is sufficient. However, the last kilometer of transportation and sale is blocked, making it difficult for them to enter the village. Some places reflect that the stock of agricultural means of production in store is less than half of that in previous years.

In addition, in some rural areas, epidemic prevention is a one-size-fits-all approach, and even blocks roads in villages, bans farmers from going to the fields, and bans agricultural machinery from going on the roads, such as spring tea picking and vegetable harvesting. These agricultural activities can not be carried out normally. Especially at present, the problem of expensive and difficult employment of agricultural workers is quite prominent, which also affects the normal agricultural activities of some large-scale operators.
